@abc-hy your simulation is diverging at time = 189.841s.
You should look at the output (exodus file) and see what the variables are doing close to then
You can also output the material properties to exodus to examine those

I suggest you write your own interface kernel deriving from InterfaceKernel without modifying the existing PenaltyInterfaceDiffusion. PenaltyInterfaceDiffusion is used to enforce the equal (jump) value constraint on the variables. In your new class, the residual on element and neighbor will be something like :
r = _test[_i][_qp] * (exp(_u[_qp] - _neighbor_value[_qp]));

and
r = _test_neighbor[_i][_qp] * (exp(_u[_qp] - _neighbor_value[_qp]));

Double check the sign in those residual. I am not quite understand your definition of normal, e.g. the convention for the direction definition.
You need to derive the Jacobian as well, e.g., take the derivative of r respect to _u and _neighbor_value.

Thanks jiangwen for the prompt reply. I checked my residual and Jacobian again, I think it's fine which I post below, in case I did something wrong:
my RESIDUAL:
jump_value =  exp(_u[_qp] - _neighbor_value[_qp]);
switch (type)
{
case Moose::Element:
r = _test[_i][_qp] * _penalty * jump_value;
break;
case Moose::Neighbor:
  r = _test_neighbor[_i][_qp] * -_penalty * jump_value ;
  break;

}
my JACOBIAN:
switch (type)
{
case Moose::ElementElement:
jac = _test[_i][_qp] * _penalty * _phi[_j][_qp] * exp(_u[_qp] - _neighbor_value[_qp]);
break;
case Moose::ElementNeighbor:
  jac = _test[_i][_qp] * _penalty * -_phi_neighbor[_j][_qp] * exp(_u[_qp] - _neighbor_value[_qp]);
  break;

case Moose::NeighborElement:
  jac = _test_neighbor[_i][_qp] * -_penalty * _phi[_j][_qp] * exp(_u[_qp] - _neighbor_value[_qp]);
  break;

case Moose::NeighborNeighbor:
  jac = _test_neighbor[_i][_qp] * -_penalty * -_phi_neighbor[_j][_qp] * exp(_u[_qp] - _neighbor_value[_qp]);
  break;

}
Also I tested other formula e.g. _u[_qp]*_u[_qp}-_u_neighbor[_qp], which works fine. But when it comes to exponential or sin or square function, it becomes non convergence.
